(5444, 'and will never be granted to no creature.*', 3779, 3),
(5445, 'e che mai accorderà ad un essere umano!', 3779, 4),
(5446, 'Lastu ashukku abadan fii kawnii', 3780, 1),
(5447, 'En aucun instant je ne doute de ma qualité de résident avec le NOVATEUR -', 3780, 2),
(5448, 'In any circumstance have I doubt my capacity to live with the Innovative -', 3780, 3),
(5449, 'Non ho mai dubitato delle mie qualità di vicino del Creatore', 3780, 4),
(5450, 'Jaaral badiihi hajaban lil kawni', 3781, 1),
(5451, 'que Sa Création est Admirable !', 3781, 2),
(5452, 'that His creation is Wonderful!', 3781, 3),
(5453, 'perché sono stato meravigliato dall\'Universo.', 3781, 4),
(5454, 'Innal lazii minal ilaahi huztu', 3782, 1),
(5455, 'Les Faveurs que j\'ai obtenues de DIEU n\'existaient nulle part dans l\'univers;', 3782, 2),
(5456, 'The Favors I obtained from GOD exist anywhere in the universe,', 3782, 3),
(5457, 'I favori che ho ottenuto da Allah non esistevano in questo Universo.', 3782, 4),
(5458, 'Haaba hanil kawni wa fiihi fuztu', 3783, 1),
(5459, 'et c\'est en cela que consiste mon succès...', 3783, 2),
(5460, 'and this is where my success is .', 3783, 3),
(5461, 'E\' in ciò che ho avuto successo.', 3783, 4),
(5462, 'Dallaniyal laahu halal laahi bilaa', 3784, 1),
(5463, 'DIEU m\'a LUI-MEME Dirigé vers DIEU, sans illusion aucune,', 3784, 2),
(5464, 'GOD HIMSELF Led me to GOD, with no illusions,', 3784, 3),
(5465, 'Che Allah mi sia guida verso Allah senza illusioni', 3784, 4),
(5466, 'Tagharrurin wa humurii taqabbalaa', 3785, 1),
(5467, 'et a agréé toute mon existence.', 3785, 2),
(5468, 'and has approved all my life.', 3785, 3),
(5469, 'e che approvi la mia vita.', 3785, 4),
(5470, 'Khaabat qulaatiya mahal hussaadi', 3786, 1),
(5471, 'Mes ennemis et les envieux ont tous été déçus dans leur attente', 3786, 2),
(5472, 'My enemies and the envious were all disappointed in their expectations', 3786, 3),
(5473, 'Che coloro che mi odiano e sono gelosi di me siano disillusi nelle loro aspettative', 3786, 4),
(5474, 'Muz samanii huztu bilaa kasaadi', 3787, 1),
(5475, 'tandis que j\'ai impétré le Prix de mon Service sans aucune sorte de faillite', 3787, 2),
(5476, 'while I Award the recipient of my service without any kind of bankruptcy.', 3787, 3),
(5477, 'e che io ottenga il mio premio senza conoscere sconfitta.', 3787, 4),
(5478, 'Wa qaaniyal baaqii bihi subuuraa', 3788, 1),
(5479, 'Grâce au Coran, DIEU, le SUBSISTANT, m\'a préservé contre toute ruine', 3788, 2),
(5480, 'Thanks to the Koran, God, The Remaining, preserved me against all ruin', 3788, 3),
(5481, 'Che l\'Eterno, grazie al Corano, mi preservi dal male', 3788, 4),
(5482, 'Tijaaratii ladayhi lan tabuuraa', 3789, 1),
(5483, 'et ma Transaction auprès de LUI ne connaîtra jamais de mévente.', 3789, 2),
(5484, 'and my transaction with HIM will never slump of.', 3789, 3),
(5485, 'e che io non conosca nessuna perdita nei miei commerci.', 3789, 4),
(5486, 'Lam yanhunii maa baaha hannil laahu', 3790, 1),
(5487, 'De par Son Infinie Grâce et par la formule « Laa ilaaha illa Laah »,', 3790, 2),
(5488, 'By His Grace and Infinite by the phrase \"Laa ilaaha illa Laah\"', 3790, 3),
(5489, 'Nella Sua grazia e in considerazione della Professione di Fede,', 3790, 4),
(5490, 'Fadlan walaa ilaaha illal laahu', 3791, 1),
(5491, 'Dieu ne permettra jamais que mon âme s\'écarte loin de ma personne.', 3791, 2),
(5492, 'God will never allow my soul deviate far from my person.', 3791, 3),
(5493, 'che Allah allontani da me ogni calunnia.', 3791, 4),
(5494, 'Yaquudu lii bilan tihaa-in samanii', 3792, 1),
(5495, 'DIEU, CELUI-LA Qui reste en ma faveur, m\'a rétribué du Salaire [de mon Service pour le Prophète]', 3792, 2),
(5496, 'God, he who remains in my favor, I paid the salary [of my service to the Prophet],', 3792, 3),
(5497, 'Che Colui che è con me mi dia per sempre il premio che merito', 3792, 4),
(5498, 'Man kaana lii wa liya saffaa zamanii', 3793, 1),
(5499, 'et, par ma personne, a purifié notre époque.', 3793, 2),
(5500, 'and my person has purified our age.', 3793, 3),
(5501, 'e che purifichi per me la nostra epoca.', 3793, 4),
(5502, 'Jaawartu rabbii bilisaanil harabi', 3794, 1),
(5503, 'Je résiderai éternellement avec mon SEIGNEUR grâce au [Saint Livre écrit] en langue arabe', 3794, 2),
(5504, 'I will dwell forever with my Lord through the [Holy Book written] in Arabic', 3794, 3),
(5505, 'Possa io essere sempre il vicino del mio Signore attraverso la lingua araba', 3794, 4),
(5506, 'Bilaa nihaayatin wa taabat qurabii', 3795, 1),
(5507, 'et excellente reste ma Proximité avec LUI.', 3795, 2),
(5508, 'and is excellent with me near HIM.', 3795, 3),
(5509, 'e che la prossimità con Allah sia eccellente.', 3795, 4),
(5510, 'Nazaha lil islaama hinda ghurbatii', 3796, 1),
(5511, 'DIEU, CELUI-LA Qui a illuminé mon âme, m\'a confié l\'Islam', 3796, 2),
(5512, 'God, he who has enlightened my soul, has entrust me Islam', 3796, 3),
(5513, 'Che Colui che ha illuminato il mio paese faciliti i miei rapporti con l\'Islam', 3796, 4),
(5514, 'Ladal jazaa-iri muniiru turbatii', 3797, 1),
(5515, 'en dépôt au cours de mon Exil dans les îles.', 3797, 2),
(5516, 'in deposit during my exile in the islands.', 3797, 3),
(5517, 'nel mio esilio, nelle isole.', 3797, 4),
(5518, 'Nuziha lii nuurul lisaani wal kitaab', 3798, 1),
(5519, 'IL n\'a cessé d\'inonder mon être de la Lumière de la langue arabe et celle du Saint Livre', 3798, 2),
(5520, 'It has continued to flood my being the Light of Arabic and the Holy Book', 3798, 3),
(5521, 'Che la luce della lingua araba e del Libro mi inondino', 3798, 4),
(5522, 'Azmaana khidmatii ladaa ahlil kitaab', 3799, 1),
(5523, 'tout le temps de mon Service pour le Prophète parmi les gens du Livre ( les colons).', 3799, 2),
(5524, 'every time during my Service to the Prophet among the people of the Book (the colonists).', 3799, 3),
(5525, 'durante il tempo del mio servizio per il Profeta malgrado la presenza dei colonizzatori.', 3799, 4),
(5526, 'Taz-yiilu maa sabata lil mushaffahi', 3800, 1),
(5527, 'La Révélation de la Vérité Intangible (le Coran) faite à Muhammad, l\'Intercesseur Agréé,', 3800, 2),
(5528, 'The Revelation of Truth Intangible (the Quran) to Muhammad, the Intercessor Dealer,', 3800, 3),
(5529, 'Che la rivelazione della certezza fatta all\'Intercessore', 3800, 4),
(5530, 'Aghnaa yamiinii han azan wa midfahi', 3801, 1),
(5531, 'me suffit comme Bouclier contre les dommages et les canons.', 3801, 2),
(5532, 'is enough for me as a shield against damage and the guns.', 3801, 3),
(5533, 'mi faccia da scudo contro le persecuzioni e i cannoni.', 3801, 4),
(5534, 'Hadaa niyal laahu wa zahzahal lahiin', 3802, 1),
(5535, 'DIEU m\'a Dirigé et a chassé hors de mon existence Satan le Réprouvé;', 3802, 2),
(5536, 'GOD Directed and has chased out of my life satan, the Forsaken;', 3802, 3),
(5537, 'Dio mi ha diretto e ha cacciato del mio esistenza Satana il reietto', 3802, 4),
(5538, 'Ilaa siwaa humriya habbazal muhiin', 3803, 1),
(5539, 'quel Excellent AUXILIAIRE!', 3803, 2),
(5540, 'How AUXILIARY Excellent!', 3803, 3),
(5541, 'Che il migliore Ausiliario!', 3803, 4),
(5542, 'ϻ?1. al hamdu lil haqqil mubiin man kawnuhu liya yabiin', 3804, 1),
(5543, 'Gloire à la VÉRITÉ Manifeste [DIEU], LUI Dont la Disponibilité en ma faveur est certaine,', 3804, 2),
(5544, 'Glory to the Obvious TRUTH [GOD], HIM Of whom the Availability in my favor is certain,', 3804, 3),
(5545, 'Halal kitaabil mustabiin maha jamiihin nihami', 3805, 1),
(5546, 'par le Livre Évident [le CORAN], de même que par l\'ensemble des Bienfaits.', 3805, 2),
(5547, 'by the Obvious Book [ the Qura\'n], as well as by all the Benefactions.', 3805, 3),
(5548, 'Ahmadu rabbiyal haziim hamdan kasiiran laa yariim', 3806, 1),
(5549, 'Je loue mon SEIGNEUR, l\'INCOMMENSURABLE, d\'une louange surabondante et sans fin,', 3806, 2),
(5550, 'I praise my Lord, the immeasurable, a superabundant and endless praise,', 3806, 3),
(5551, 'Musalliyan halaa kariim qaadal waraa lil munhimi', 3807, 1),
(5552, 'en priant sur le Noble qui a dirigé la créature vers CELUI Qui accorde les Bienfaits.', 3807, 2),
(5553, 'praying on the Noble who headed  the creature towards the ONE Who grants Benefits.', 3807, 3),
(5554, 'Ashkuru zal harshil majiid shukran yulaaqiihi maziid', 3808, 1),
(5555, 'Je rends grâce au MAITRE du Trône Glorieux, d\'une reconnaissance qui implique l\'augmentation des bienfaits,', 3808, 2),
(5556, 'I thank the MASTER of the Glorious Throne, a recognition which involves increased benefits,', 3808, 3),
(5557, 'Musalliman halal wahiid bikalkalii wa kaliimii', 3809, 1),
(5558, 'en adressant le Salut à Celui qui est Unique, par mon coeur et mes paroles.', 3809, 2),
(5559, 'by addressing the salute to Him who is Unique, by my heart and my words.', 3809, 3),
(5560, 'Shakartuhu iz khassanii bikhidmatil maahis sanii', 3810, 1),
(5561, 'Je LUI témoigne gratitude, car IL m\'a particularisé par le service de l\'Effaceur Sublime,', 3810, 2),
(5562, 'I testify gratitude HIM because HE me particularized by the service of the Sublime Eraser,', 3810, 3),
(5563, 'Zaa khidmatin fil halanii lahu wa fakka walami', 3811, 1),
(5564, 'en Lui rendant service manifestement, Lui qui a brisé mon carcan.', 3811, 2),
(5565, 'by doing a service to Him obviously, Him who broke my yoke.', 3811, 3),
(5566, 'Lahu khitaabii daahiyaa bimaa yuhibbu maadiyaa', 3812, 1),
(5567, 'C\'est à Lui que s\'adressent mes propos, appelant à ce qui fut son Voeu,', 3812, 2),
(5568, 'It is to Him that my remarks are addressed, calling for what was his Vow,', 3812, 3),
(5569, 'Wa qaada lii aghraadiyaa zaadan lidaaril karami', 3813, 1),
(5570, 'Il m\'a octroyé ce que je désirais en provisions pour la Demeure Honorable.', 3813, 2),
(5571, 'He granted me what I wanted as provisions for the Honorable House.', 3813, 3),
(5572, 'Yaa rabbanaa yaa rabbanaa yaa rabbanaa yaa rabbanaa', 3814, 1),
(5573, 'Ô TOI notre SEIGNEUR ! Ô TOI notre SEIGNEUR! Ô Toi notre SEIGNEUR ! Ô TOI notre SEIGNEUR !', 3814, 2),
(5574, 'O YOU our Lord! O YOU our Lord! O YOU our Lord! O YOU our Lord!', 3814, 3),
(5575, 'Yaa rabbanash kur sah-yanaa bil muntaqal muhtarami', 3815, 1),
(5576, 'Ô TOI notre SEIGNEUR ! accepte notre action, par la Grâce du Sélectionné qui est le Vénérable.', 3815, 2),
(5577, 'O YOU our Lord! accept our action, by the Grace of the  Selected who is Venerable.', 3815, 3),
(5578, 'Lil mustafal lazii turaam lahu salaatun wa salaam', 3816, 1),
(5579, 'Chaque année, au moment de mon éloge, je sollicite la Prière et le Salut', 3816, 2),
(5580, 'Every year, at the time of my eulogy, I request the Prayer and the Safety', 3816, 3),
(5581, 'Maham tidaahi kulla haam rumtu minal mukarrimi', 3817, 1),
(5582, 'de CELUI QUI HONORE (Al Mukarrimi), en faveur de l\'Élu le Plus Pur (Al Mustafaa) sur qui on prie.', 3817, 2),
(5583, 'Of the ONE WHO is HONORED (Al Mukarrimi), in favour of the Purest Elected representative (Al Mustafaa) on whom we pray.', 3817, 3),
(5584, 'Salli halaa manin jahal qutbal wujuudi hiina hal', 3818, 1),
(5585, 'Prie sur Celui qui est fait Pôle de l\'Univers dès qu\'Il est venu,', 3818, 2),
(5586, 'Pray on the One who is made Pole of the Universe as soon as He came,', 3818, 3),
(5587, 'Wa aalihi zawin nihal wa sahbihi wa karrimi', 3819, 1),
(5588, 'sur sa famille, les possesseurs des dons et sur ses compagnons et honore-les tous.', 3819, 2),
(5589, 'On his family, the owners of the donations and on his companions and honor them all.', 3819, 3),
(5590, 'Salli halaa man juhilaa khayra nabbiyin fuddilaa', 3820, 1),
(5591, 'Prie sur Celui qui est fait Meilleur Prophète, rendu Précellent', 3820, 2),
(5592, 'Pray on the One who is made Better Prophet, made Most Better', 3820, 3),
(5593, 'Hiina abuunan jadalaa fii tiinihi wa hazzimi', 3821, 1),
(5594, 'lorsque l\'Aïeul était voilé dans la boue, et glorifie-Le.', 3821, 2),
(5595, 'when the Grandfather was veiled in the mud, and glorify him.', 3821, 3),
(5596, 'Wa salliman yaa rabbiyaa halaa khitaamil anbiyaa', 3822, 1),
(5597, 'Et accorde un Salut - Ô SEIGNEUR! - au Sceau des Prophètes', 3822, 2),
(5598, 'And grant a Salute - O LORD! - for the Seal of the Prophets', 3822, 3),
(5599, 'Wal mursaliinal asfiyaa imaaminal muhazzami', 3823, 1),
(5600, 'et Envoyés qui sont les purs, Lui qui est notre Vénérable Guide.', 3823, 2),
(5601, 'and Messengers which are the pure, Him who is our Respectable Guide.', 3823, 3),
(5602, 'Wa salli yaa zan nihmati halaa rasuulir rahmati', 3824, 1),
(5603, 'Et accorde une Prière - Ô MAITRE des Bienfaits! - à l\'Envoyé de la Miséricorde,', 3824, 2),
(5604, 'And grant a Prayer - O Master of Benefits! - The Messenger of Mercy,', 3824, 3),
(5605, 'Mighlaaqi baabin niqmati sababi kulli nasami', 3825, 1),
(5606, 'Celui qui verrouille la porte du châtiment, Lui qui est la raison d\'être de toute créature.', 3825, 2),
(5607, 'the One that locks the door of punishment, He who is the reason of being of all creation.', 3825, 3),
(5608, 'Wa salliman yaa samadii halan nabii muhammadi', 3826, 1),
(5609, 'Puis accorde Ton Salut - Ô TOI le SOUTIEN UNIVERSEL! - au Prophète Mouhammad,', 3826, 2),
(5610, 'Then grant Your Salute - O YOU the UNIVERSAL SUPPORT! - To the Prophet Muhammad,', 3826, 3),
(5611, 'Wa aalihi wal hummadi wa kun lizit tarassumi', 3827, 1),
(5612, 'à sa famille, ainsi qu\'aux laudateurs [de DIEU] et sois en la faveur de celui qui suit les Traces.', 3827, 2),
(5613, 'his family, as well as admirers [of God] and be in favor of the one who follows the traces.', 3827, 3),
(5614, 'Yaa zal baqaa wal qidami minnii taqabbal khidamii', 3828, 1),
(5615, 'Ô TOI le SUBSISTANT et le PRIMORDIAL! Agrée mes services', 3828, 2),
(5616, 'O YOU and the REMAINING ESSENTIAL! Approve my services', 3828, 3),
(5617, 'Wal turdi zat taqaddumi bihaa muniirul laqami', 3829, 1),
(5618, 'et fais les accepter par le Prééminent, Ô TOI Qui as illuminé mon sentier!', 3829, 2),
(5619, 'and do accept them by the Preeminent, O YOU who have illuminated my path!', 3829, 3),
(5620, 'Zaaka khiyaarul harabi zaaka muniilul arabi', 3830, 1),
(5621, 'Celui-là est la Fleur des arabes, Celui-là est le Pourvoyeur des besoins,', 3830, 2),
(5622, 'This one is the Flower of the Arabs, this one is the Sustainer of needs,', 3830, 3),
(5623, 'Zaaka sabiilut talabi tabiibu ahlis saqami', 3831, 1),
(5624, 'Celui-là est la Voie de la Sollicitude, Il est la Thérapeutique des personnes malades.', 3831, 2),
(5625, 'This one is the Way of Care, He is the Therapeutic of sick people.', 3831, 3),
(5626, 'Salli halaa baabil hudaa naa-il madaa muulin nadaa', 3832, 1),
(5627, 'Accorde Prière à Celui qui est la Porte de la Rectitude, à Celui dont l\'Influence est Vaste,', 3832, 2),
(5628, 'Grant Prayer to Him who is the Gate of Righteousness, to one whose influence is vast,', 3832, 3),
(5629, 'Laysil hidaa maahir radaa baabil hulaa wal karami', 3833, 1),
(5630, 'à Celui qui favorise en Dons, le Lion des ennemis, le Dissipateur du péril, la Porte de l\'Eminence et de l\'Honneur.', 3833, 2),
(5631, 'the One who favors with donations, the Lion of the enemies, the sink of danger, the Gate of Eminence and Honor.', 3833, 3),
(5632, 'Wa salliman halal amiin zaakal makiinu wal matiin', 3834, 1),
(5633, 'Accorde Ton Salut à l\'Intègre (Al Amîn), Haut Placé (Auprès de DIEU) et Solide,', 3834, 2),
(5634, 'Grant Your Salute to the Integrate (Al Amin), High Placed, (near GOD) and Solid,', 3834, 3),
(5635, 'Zaakal mujiiru wal qamiin bizas sanaa wahtarimi', 3835, 1),
(5636, 'Celui-là est le Protecteur et il est Celui qui est Digne de cet éloge, et honore-Le.', 3835, 2),
(5637, 'This one is the Protector, and He is who is worthy of this praise, and honor Him.', 3835, 3),
(5638, 'Zaakal wahiidu wal majiid wahwal mabbarru wal ahiid', 3836, 1),
(5639, 'Celui-là est Unique et Glorieux, il est Pieux et Singulier,', 3836, 2),
(5640, 'This one is unique and Glorious, Pious and He is singular,', 3836, 3),
(5641, 'Man bis tiqaamatin yaquud ilal jinaani man hami', 3837, 1),
(5642, 'Lui qui dirige par la Rectitude l\'aveugle vers le Paradis.', 3837, 2),
(5643, 'He who directs the blindman straightness to Paradise.', 3837, 3),
(5644, 'Salli wa sallim yaa qadiir halaa siraajikal muniir', 3838, 1),
(5645, 'Ô TOI le PUISSANT! accorde Prière et Salut à Ton Flambeau qui illumine;', 3838, 2),
(5646, 'O YOU THE POWERFUL! Grant Prayer and Salute to Your Torch that illuminates;', 3838, 3),
(5647, 'Wahwal bashiiru wan naziir biniqamin wa nihami', 3839, 1);
INSERT INTO `trans` (`id`, `trans`, `bayite_id`, `langue_id`) VALUES
(5648, 'Celui-là est l\'Annonciateur des Bonnes Nouvelles par le Bienfait et l\'Avertisseur par le Châtiment.', 3839, 2),
(5649, 'This one is the Bringer of Good News by the blessing and warning by the Punishment.', 3839, 3),
(5650, 'Zaakal rasuulur rahati wa zaaka rahbur rahati', 3840, 1),
(5651, 'Celui-là est l\'Envoyé de la Quiétude, c\'est Celui qui a la Main Généreuse', 3840, 2),
(5652, 'This one is the Messenger of Harmony is the one that has the Generous Hand', 3840, 3),
(5653, 'Wa zaaka zul fasaahati zaaka rassulul malhami', 3841, 1),
(5654, 'et c\'est Lui le Maître de l\'Eloquence, c\'est Lui l\'Envoyé Combattant.', 3841, 2),
(5655, 'and He is the Master of Eloquence, He is the Fighter Messenger.', 3841, 3),
(5656, 'Salli wa sallim sarmadaa yaa man kafaanii kamadaa', 3842, 1),
(5657, 'Ô TOI Qui m\'as préservé de l\'angoisse! Accorde Prière et Salut', 3842, 2),
(5658, 'O YOU who have preserved me from the anguish! Grant Prayer and Salute', 3842, 3),
(5659, 'Halal bahiiji ahmadaa wa liya kun binihami', 3843, 1),
(5660, 'au Plus Louangé (Ahmad), le Charmant, et accorde-moi des Dons copieux.', 3843, 2),
(5661, 'to the Most Praised (Ahmad), the charming and grant me generous godsends.', 3843, 3),
(5662, 'Lii jammilanna zaahirii wa baatinii bitaahiri', 3844, 1),
(5663, 'Embellis mon extérieur et mon intérieur au Nom de l\'Etre Pur,', 3844, 2),
(5664, 'Enchant my outside and inside in the Name of the Pure Being,', 3844, 3),
(5665, 'Yaa maahiyan kabaa-irii bijaahihi wa lamami', 3845, 1),
(5666, 'Ô TOI Qui, grâce à Lui, as effacé mes péchés capitaux et véniels!', 3845, 2),
(5667, 'O YOU who, through him, forgave my venial and deadly sins!', 3845, 3),
(5668, 'Yaa man ladayhi amalii hannii halal muzzammili', 3846, 1),
(5669, 'Ô TOI entre les Mains de Qui se trouve mon espoir!', 3846, 2),
(5670, 'O YOU in the hands of Whom is my hope!', 3846, 3),
(5671, 'Salli bikullil kummali maha jamiihil umami', 3847, 1),
(5672, 'Accorde de ma part Ta Prière à Celui qui est Drapé (A Muzammil), aux parfaits (compagnons), de même qu\'à l\'ensemble de la Communauté.', 3847, 2),
(5673, 'Grants from me Your prayer to Him who is Draped (A Muzammil), to the perfects (companions) as well as the whole of the Community.', 3847, 3),
(5674, 'Wa sallimanna yaa badiih halal mutaahi wal mutiih', 3848, 1),
(5675, 'Ô TOI le NOVATEUR ! accorde Ton Salut à Celui qui est Obéi et qui est Obéissant;', 3848, 2),
(5676, 'O YOU the INNOVATIVE! Grant Your Salute to Him who is Obeyed and is obedient;', 3848, 3),
(5677, 'Zaakal mushaffahush shafiih habiibikal mufakh-khami', 3849, 1),
(5678, 'Celui-là est l\'Intercesseur dont l\'Intercession est agréée, Ton Bien-Aimé Très Estimé.', 3849, 2),
(5679, 'This one is the intercessor whose intercession is approved, Your Beloved Very Estimated.', 3849, 3),
(5680, 'Salli halal mubajjali yaa man hamaa han khajali', 3850, 1),
(5681, 'Accorde Ta Prière à Celui qui est Vénérable - Ô TOI Qui m\'as préservé de la confusion!', 3850, 2),
(5682, 'Grant Your Prayer to the One woh is Venerable - O YOU who have preserved my confusion!', 3850, 3),
(5683, 'Wa hinda kamhu wa jalii wa hindahu fakh-khimi', 3851, 1),
(5684, 'Efface Auprès de TOI et auprès de Lui mon angoisse et glorifie-Le.', 3851, 2),
(5685, 'Clears Beside YOU and to Him my anguish and glorify Him.', 3851, 3),
(5686, 'Yaa rabbanaa yaa rabbanaa yaa khillanaa yaa hibbanaa', 3852, 1),
(5687, 'Ô notre SEIGNEUR! Ô notre SEIGNEUR! Ô notre AMI! Ô notre BIEN-AIME!', 3852, 2),
